.TH "cp_init" 9 "cp_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
cp_init \- allocate ccwchains for a channel program.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" cp_init
.BI "(struct channel_program *cp "  ","
.BI "struct device *mdev "  ","
.BI "union orb *orb "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cp" 12
channel_program on which to perform the operation
.IP "mdev" 12
the mediated device to perform pin/unpin operations
.IP "orb" 12
control block for the channel program from the guest
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This creates one or more ccwchain(s), and copies the raw data of
the target channel program from \fIorb->cmd.iova\fP to the new ccwchain(s).

Limitations:
1. Supports idal(c64) ccw chaining.
2. Supports 4k idaw.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success and a negative error value on failure.
